I like writing letters to old friends on behalf of good students.
 This is because I feel I am doing good service for both.
 I also like writing these letters because there are some students who I
 am only willing to send to people I trust and respect.
 Ann is one of those students and you are one of those advisors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
I have known Ann since since 2010 when David Cooper and I hired her for
 a summer of field work in Yellowstone National Park.
 She was supported by an NSF Research Experience for Undergraduates supplemental
 award.
 In January of 2012, I recruited her for a masters project in my lab, where
 she now works.
 Ann took my graduate class, 
