 I am sure she will fit in well in your lab.
 Your students will like her.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ann is now doing population modeling with me for her masters degree.
 The challenge is to formulate an age-structured, discrete time model of
 births and deaths in populations of white-tailed deer.
 This is a fairly standard task.
 What is not standard is assimilating that model with multiple sources of
 data in a way that allows true forecasts -- predictions accompanied by
 credible intervals.
 She will use the model to evaluate a range of alternatives for controlling
 growth of overabundant deer populations in national parks in the east.
 Ann has worked exceedingly hard to learn the math, statistics, and programming
 necessary to pull this off.
 She is boundlessly enthusiastic about the work, which has motivated her
 to take advanced classes in mathematical and statistical modeling, including
 a graduate level statistics class (i.e., graduate level for 
